          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2018-12-13T19:29:51Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>B-47 Ridge Designation Act</b></p> <p>This bill designates the mountain ridge that runs south and west of Emigrant Peak in the Absaroka Range in Montana, which is where an Air Force B-47 strategic bomber crashed while on a training mission in 1962, as the &quot;B-47 Ridge.&quot;</p> <p>The bill permits the installing of a plaque on the ridge in memory of such crash. </p>]]></text>
